Title: Object: A Greek caloyer
Series: Views in Egypt, Palestine and other parts of the Ottoman Empire
Description: Plate 20 in volume II: a Greek caloyer standing on a raised ground on the left, raising his right hand, looking towards four men and three women with a baby on the right; heads of men looking towards the caloyer through a fence behind him; another caloyer watching outside from a window in a tower on the right; after Mayer; published state. 1803 Hand-coloured aquatint with etching
Bibliographic references: Abbey Travel / Travel in Aquatint and lithography 1770-1860 from the library of J.R.Abbey (369.II.20)
